laboratory_examinations.findings: Normal liver without focal lesion, normal gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, and bilateral adrenal glands. Kidneys enhance and excrete contrast symmetrically. Extensive pericolonic fat stranding with an inflamed diverticulum and a focus of air adjacent, indicative of possible microperforation. No focal fluid collection, no free air or free fluid in the abdomen.
MIXED BACTERIAL FLORA (>= 3 COLONY TYPES), CONSISTENT WITH SKIN AND/OR GENITAL CONTAMINATION.
